Package: immuneSIM
Type: Package
Title: Tunable Multi-Feature Simulation of B- And T-Cell Adaptive Immune Receptor Repertoires
Version: 0.8.6
Authors@R: c(
    person("Cédric R.", "Weber", email = "cedric.weber@bsse.ethz.ch",role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Victor", "Greiff", email = "victor.greiff@medisin.uio.no",role = "aut"))
Author: Cédric R. Weber [aut, cre], Victor Greiff [aut]
Maintainer: Cédric R. Weber <cedric.weber@bsse.ethz.ch>
Description: Simulate full BCR and TCR repertoires using an in-silico recombination process that 
    includes a wide variety of tunable parameters to introduce noise and biases. Additional post-
    simulation modification functions allow the user to implant motifs or codon biases as well as 
    remodeling sequence similarity architecture. The output repertoires contain records of all 
    relevant repertoire dimensions and can be anaylzed using provided repertoire analysis functions.
Depends: R (>= 3.4.0)
Imports: poweRlaw, stringdist, Biostrings, igraph, stringr, data.table, plyr, reshape2, ggplot2,
    grid, ggthemes, RColorBrewer, Metrics, repmis
License: GPL-3
URL: https://immuneSIM.readthedocs.io
BugReports: https://github.com/GreiffLab/immuneSIM/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.1.1
